  • EASY TO USE - No special skills or tools are needed.The silicone mold making kit includes part A and part B, the mixing ratio is 1:1 by weight. Pour the Part A and Part B together, then stir 5-6 minutes, make sure to stir the mixture thoroughly for better results.
  • SAFE - Our silicone rubber is made of safe silicone material, high-quality,non-toxic and no odor, very flexible, soft and clear.
  • PREMIUM Our silicone rubber with self-debubbling,the bubbles will automatically disappear within 2 hours, no vacuum degassing is necessary. The completely cure time is about 12 hours at room temperature, it varies from your mold size and thickness.
  • WIDELY USE - Excellent for making resin molds, wax molds, candle molds, soap molds, casting molds and so on. ATTENTION:Not for making food mold use.
  • Please Note:mixing without using silicone cup and molding without using silicone or clay mold.They will fuse.

      Darlene
      4.0 out of 5 stars Great product, needs more detailed instructions
      Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2020
      Size: 21.16 ozVerified Purchase
      The only reason this product got 4 stars is because it came with no instructions on how to use, except for using it as a 1:1 ratio. I had to research how to get good results with this product.
      On the great side, this liquid silicone makes beautiful molds. Very detailed and bubble free. I've made more than just the two I pictured, and have used them quite a few times before writing this review.
      A lesson I have learned.
      As much as you think it's better and less expensive, don't use cardboard. I did on my first few molds, and it leaked if I didn't seal it enough. I lost product that way. Use foam core board. It may not be free like cardboard, but it's worth it. One sheet makes a lot of mold holders.
      A glue gun is a must. It seals all those crevices. I use 2 different types, depending on the mold I'm making.
      Don't waste space. If you can get more than one piece in a single mold, do it. I should have added more to the one I had multiple pieces in. I had too much wasted space and product.
      Because this is clear, it will be harder to judge where the material is on top of the piece you are molding. I use a pin to judge where it is, so I know if I need to add more product or not. If it has too thin and area in any spit, the mold will rip.
      All in all, I really like the product. I've had so much fun with it, and it has given me many more ideas for my resin creations.
